title: Want To Buy:  Wanted (Buy/Trade) - Marlin Model 60 w/22" Barrel - almost any condition
postcontent:
I'm looking for a specific build of the Marlin 60 22LR (which I believe is actually the most common kind). It has to be a 22" barrel and has to have a screw in front sight blade (Not the older kind where the front sight is integral to the mag tube holder). I'm not sure when the screw-on blade sight started (70's? 80's?), but the 22" barrel was reduced to 19" in the early 2000s.

Would prefer a known shooter, but will take anything with a clean bright bore and an intact bolt, receiver, and action.

Nothing else is important - shot, busted or missing stock - mag tube broken or missing or whatever. Even the barrel and receiver can be beat up and somewhat rusty on the outside. It's for a project. It doesn't even have to have the sight - that's just a way to distinguish the barrel.

FTF in Gwinnett area or any GA non-dealer private party who knows you can send longarms through the mail to other GA residents without FFL (http://www.atf.gov/content/firearms-frequently-asked-questions-unlicensed-persons#shipping-firearms-usps). No transfers - just not worth it.

Some stuff I can work into a trade.

New NIB  Ruger BX-25 Magazine
New NIB BSA laser sight LS650 (x2)
New NIB Sightmark 30-30 laser bore sight
Type 53 Mosin Nagant M44 variant - G/VG rifle with busted up/rough but shootable stock (perfect for a sporter project)
FIE CBC Single shot 12GA shotgun - minor stock crack and chunk gone out of buttplate, but good shooter.
Ammo - .22LR, 7.62x39, 7.62x54, 7.62x25, .40 S&W...
(Not huge qtys of ammo - a brick or two of 22, maybe 100 each of the others as part of a deal - not a whole gun for ammo trade).

Legendary Polish Special Forces Radom Mag-98 pistol, Used Surplus condition, Shows signs of use,shoots and groups great, wonderful modern 9mm, very rare accepts Beretta and Taurus mags...
The Polish MAG 98 9mm /9x19 NATO caliber pistol is an improved variation of the original Polish MAG95. 
It was produced for the Polish Special Forces, Border Guard and Prison Guard (StraÅ¼ WiÄ™zienna) in the 1990's. 
Made in the Z.M. Lucznik factory 11 at Radom Poland. 

These fine pistols feature a ambidextrous decocker safety, steel slide, alloy frame, and serrated trigger guard front strap.
In 1996 the Mag 98 was evaluated for adoption purposes by the Polish Army. It had advantages over its competition such as 
better reliability, durability and safety (better protection against accidental discharge, when dropped). 

Although the quality was deemed superior,  the MAG 98 was rejected by the Army because the frame was slightly larger
than  the contract qualifications called for. That was a shame because most service members prefered it and in fact 
the pistol has a good reputation among users: It is considered a precise, well balanced and durable weapon 
and its mass leads to good stability during firing.

title: For Sale:  Russian Makarov Pistol - Hi-Cap Model w/spare mags, holster & tools
postcontent:
This is a Russian Makarov pistol in the traditional 9x18 caliber. It is in excellent physical and mechanical condition with a perfect bore. These pistols were imported from Russia by KBI for several years in the 90's and there was two versions: the first was the standard pistol that used a single stack magazine, and the other was a high capacity model that used a double stack 10 round magazine giving it an 11 round total capacity. 

The pistol for sale here is the high capacity model and far fewer of these were brought over making it much more scarce and sought after. Pistol fires single action or double action. It has fully adjustable rear sights and is surprisingly accurate for a military firearm. It also has a hammer block type safety that allows it to be carried with a loaded chamber.

Pistol comes with it's original inner and outer factory box with all the factory literature that was shipped with it. It also comes with three 10 round hi-cap magazines, an original Russian leather holster with matching lanyard (both in excellent condition), the original cleaning rod, plus the multi tool that was supplied by the factory.

Price is $475. FTF only with pickup in Brandon. You must be a Florida resident and at least 21 to purchase. A bill of sale will be provided. 

Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Sino-Soviet Triangle 26 SKS (1958) in Excellent Condition
postcontent:
Sino-Soviet Jianshe Arsenal (Triangle 26) SKS. Based on S/N, this rifle should have been manufactured in 1958. The SKS rifle was first made at the Jianshe Arsenal in 1956 under close Soviet supervision, which resulted in quality comparable to the Soviet made rifles.

Parts are milled, not stamped. It has the heavy barrel lug and threaded barrel, unlike the light weight lug and pinned barrels of the Norincos. Early Chinese SKS rifles also came standard with the Soviet style blade bayonet, as shown, instead of the later Chinese spike bayonet. This one is very clean, rust free, and in excellent condition. Barrel is bright and shiny. It hasn't been shot since it was imported to the US in the late 80's. I am the second owner since import.

I own a few Soviet made rifles and I can attest that the steel parts in this rifle look and fit as good as those in my Tulas. These oldest Chinese rifles are hard to find and collectors are holding on to them, so this rifle would make a nice addition to any serious SKS collection.

Face to face in Winston-Salem area only. Must have CCW or Pistol Permit to buy. We'll do bill of sale.

Price is $550.00.

title: For Sale:  kel tec PF9 Great Condition Everything Factory Included. Price Firm !!
location: South OKC, Central OKC, Oklahoma City, Oklahoma
postcontent:
Have a Great Condition Kel Tec PF9 9mm up for Sale. About 1 year old. Quite possibly the best carry gun made. Super thin and light. Low count, less then 100 rounds through the gun !!

 Done a few things to the gun to improve it. A Kel-Tec is meant to be "finished" by the owner for the most part. All modifications are easily reversible but I doubt you'd want to.

 **This gun shoots MUCH nicer than a stock factory gun.**

 - Fluff and Buffed. Gun has been broken down and deburred. Slide rails and feed ramp smoothed. Hammer surface smoothed

 - Trigger straightened, softened and shortened. Biggest complaint with this gun is the trigger shape from the factory can "pinch" larger fingers. 

 The shorter trigger is MUCH more controllable and softer to shoot. A stock replacement trigger is about 2 bucks from Kel-Tec.

 - Hogue grip installed and trimmed. Helps suck up the recoil and improve grip on this little beast.

 - +1 extended magazine bottom not only adds a round but vastly improves the gun grip.

 - Extra +1 magazine. Any defensive gun needs an extra mag. It also has the +1 extension

 - Sights and hammer painted orange. For some reason the white sights and my eyes did not play nicely. Orange is MUCH easier to see and get on target with. Orange hammer means it is much easier to stage the trigger (along with the shortened trigger) for fast accurate shots. Both are "painted" with orange nail polish. It's the type that doesn't need remover. Just "peels" off with a toothpick if you don't dig orange. You will though.

 - Shimmed rear site. Gun was accurate but this shooter always trended a touch low with it. You may be different. Shim is just a plastic spacer that you can remove if you shoot differently than I do. I'm no marksman.

 - Deburred the grip. Has some ridges on it from the factory that can hurt your hands after awhile. An hour with an emery board really smoothed things out.

 Also included:

 Kel-Tec plastic case

 Instruction booklets

 Face To Face Cash Sale and Buyer Need to Sign Bill of Sale. 
 With Valid State of Oklahoma DL or State ID required to prove of age.

 Need to be 18 Years Old to buy and own a firearm !!

 Seller has the right Not to Sell the Firearm to anyone without Prejudice !!

 Asking $350 Firm !! Because the gun has Laserlyte side Laser ($80) installed recently!!

 Sunday is my Only Day off, I could meet in Oklahoma City.

title: For Sale:  PX-22 Pistol - .22LR Semi-Auto
postcontent:
This PX-22 pistol was made in the USA by American Arms, and is essentially a copy of the ERMA Werkes EP522 which happens to closely resemble the Walther PPK only much smaller. In fact the PX-22's frame was made by American Arms, however the slide, barrel and magazine was made in Germany by ERMA. The pistols were assembled and then sold here in the US by American Arms. The factory magazines are stamped "ERMA" and the slide is also stamped Design by ERMA.

This pistol is used but in excellent condition and I would rate it's overall condition at 95%. It fires any .22LR ammo and uses a 7 round magazine. It is single or double action and has a hammer block mechanism making it safe to carry with a round in the chamber which gives it a total capacity of 8 rounds (7+1).

Bottom line is that the PX-22 is an Ultra Compact semi-auto pistol that would be perfect for concealed carry, nightstand or glovebox use. When loaded with the Interceptor or Stinger type ammo it would also pack a big punch for a very small package.

Pistol comes with it's original instruction manual, a brand new Bianchi belt clip holster (paid $25), brand new factory spare finger rest magazine (paid $50), and 200 rounds of ammo as pictured (paid $30).

Asking price for everything is $325. FTF only with pickup in the Valrico/Brandon area. You must be at least 21 and a Florida resident to purchase - no exceptions. A proper bill of sale will be provided.
